c. Handling Outliers

In [25]:
# Handling outliers
# Calculate IQR for 'Age' and 'Fare'
Q1 = df[['Age', 'Fare']].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df[['Age', 'Fare']].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
In [26]:
# Define lower and upper bounds for outlier detection
lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
In [27]:
lower_bound
Out[27]:
Age      2.500
Fare   -26.724
dtype: float64
In [28]:
upper_bound
Out[28]:
Age     54.5000
Fare    65.6344
dtype: float64
In [29]:
# Replace outliers with NaN in 'Age' column
df['Age'] = np.where((df['Age'] < lower_bound['Age']) | (df['Age'] > upper_bound['Age']), np.nan, df['Age'])
In [30]:
# Replace outliers with NaN in 'Fare' column
df['Fare'] = np.where((df['Fare'] < lower_bound['Fare']) | (df['Fare'] > upper_bound['Fare']), np.nan, df['Fare'])
In [31]:
# Handle missing values in 'Age' column using median
median_age = df['Age'].median()

In [32]:
